Kelsey Plum has made college basketball history. 
The University of Washington senior scored 57 points on Saturday to break the NCAA women's basketball all-time scoring record, previously held by Jackie Stiles. 
Her 57-point performance was also the fifth-most in a game in women's Division I history, according to ESPN Stats & Info. With this basket, Kelsey Plum is the new all-time scoring leader in women's college basketball. #PlumsPursuit https://t.co/FIxQjwUg4g — Washington WBB (@UW_WBB) February 25, 2017 Kelsey Plum checks out of the ball game as the new all-time NCAA scoring leader. #PlumsPursuit pic.twitter.com/jWbeIv1aCe — Washington WBB (@UW_WBB) February 25, 2017
